@sgouezel I added `equivCoxeterGroup` to the current branch which is based on #9185 and #9403 

However, I am still stuck at trying to prove `Injective cs`.  With what I currently have, I would need to show that `Injective (PresentedGroup.of (rels := CoxeterGroup.Relations.toSet M)`.  I was looking over mathlib and trying to find some inspiration, and saw the ping pong lemma in `CoprodI.lean` which shows that `Injective (FreeGroup \alpha ->* G)` but it has many assumptions (disjoint etc) so AFAICT it wouldn't be applicable for Coxeter groups.  Other than that, I am wondering if I need to do something similar to `FreeGroup \alpha` where the word reductions for the Coxeter groups are what would make the hom injective?  

Any suggestions?
